      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1779077030745,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "text": "Trigger                                        →   What gets collected\n────────────────────────────────────────       ─────────────────────────────────────────────\nUser drops scene reference                     →   Registry GC'd (host's WeakMap entry releases)\nUser disposes renderer                         →   All registries for that renderer GC'd\nUser disposes texture                          →   defaultMaterials entry GC'd (WeakMap key)\nUser disposes material                         →   We dispose batches via dispose event; sprites resurrect or fall back\nSprite removed from scene                      →   registry.sprites delete on 'removed' event; batch slot freed next sweep\n\nNo finalization machinery, no polling, no explicit teardown the user has to remember. WeakMap chains do the work.",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Trigger                                        →   What gets collected\n────────────────────────────────────────       ─────────────────────────────────────────────\nUser drops scene reference                     →   Registry GC'd (host's WeakMap entry releases)\nUser disposes renderer                         →   All registries for that renderer GC'd\nUser disposes texture                          →   defaultMaterials entry GC'd (WeakMap key)\nUser disposes material                         →   We dispose batches via dispose event; sprites resurrect or fall back\nSprite removed from scene                      →   registry.sprites delete on 'removed' event; batch slot freed next sweep\n\nNo finalization machinery, no polling, no explicit teardown the user has to remember. WeakMap chains do the work.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "baseline": 11,
      "index": "aQ"
    }
  ],
